Odisha
Aug 30, 2014
Child Sexual Abuse, Rape
Description:
			A tea-stall owner of Bhanjnagar in Ganjam district was arrested today for allegedly raping a six-year-old girl last week.

The accused was identified as Siba Sahu (22), an unmarried person, sub-divisional police officer, Bhanjanagar R C Sethi said.

The girl had gone to his shop to buy milk when Sahu allegedly lured the student of standard I with chocolate and raped her.

The victim's father lodged an FIR after the girl narrated the incident, police said.


